Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Senior Backend Software Engineer position with Atomic Semi. I bring over three years of professional experience in backend systems, real-time orchestration, and AI/ML infrastructure, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the technical depth and systems fundamentals this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected high-performance backend APIs using Python and FastAPI that power an MCP AI interaction layer, translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and failure recovery mechanisms across a distributed microservices surface. I designed data models for complex workflows (tool schemas, execution runs, validation states) that enable real-time orchestration of concurrent multi-agent systems using LangChain and LangGraph, directly mirroring the data modeling challenges (recipes, runs, tools, wafers, jobs) central to Atomic Semi's fab software. To keep these systems production-ready, I built a full observability layer using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks — reducing latency by 60% and API costs by 50% through targeted concurrency and performance tuning optimizations. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs — giving me direct, hands-on experience with backend architecture, database internals, and cloud-native system design. I also developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to handle long-running data import jobs and prevent Lambda timeouts, ensuring reliability and failure recovery for mission-critical operations. Together, these roles have prepared me to lead the architecture and development of high-performance backend APIs (Go, Rust, gRPC) that power Atomic Semi's central fab product and contribute meaningfully to bridging the gap between web applications and physical manufacturing hardware.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in systems-level programming, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical leadership — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and hands-on culture Atomic Semi values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for model training and fine-tuning. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle — from data preparation and training runs to inference optimization using vLLM and deployment via Hugging Face — ensuring both performance and reliability of mission-critical inference systems. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the technical communication and leadership responsibilities valued in senior engineering roles. Additionally, my personal project, Dark Factory, demonstrates my commitment to systems-level programming and distributed systems: I built an orchestrator for AI coding CLIs using Rust, implementing full CLI IO ownership via PTY and secure distributed coordination across machines using Y-crdt for real-time state synchronization. This hands-on, build-it-ourselves approach aligns perfectly with Atomic Semi's philosophy that "building it ourselves is better" and the belief that "our team and fab can build anything."

I have always been passionate about pushing the limits of technology through hands-on engineering and building systems from first principles, and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering Atomic Semi's mission of building a small, fast semiconductor fab that makes chip manufacturing programmable, observable, and software-defined. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

